-- Hong Kong Woman Missing in Philippines for 11 Days, Morning Post Reports
-- B y   S t a n l e y   J a m e s
-- 2010-09-23T22:54:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-23/hong-kong-woman-missing-in-philippines-for-11-days-morning-post-reports.html
A Hong Kong woman has been missing
for 11 days in the Philippines, the South China Morning Post
reported, citing her family and friends.  Carole Day was last seen in Manila on Sept. 12 by a
business partner, Tschai Ma, in the city’s Makati business
district, according to the report.  Jai Day, 24, the woman’s son, flew to Manila yesterday to
try to find his mother after speaking to the Philippine and Hong
Kong police, according to the report. Carole Day was due to
return to Hong Kong Sept. 15 to attend a funeral, the report
said, citing her friend and business associate Mina Mahtani.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stanley James at 
 sjames8@bloomberg.net  